Within an OpenSSH configuration, which option disables the use of empty passwords?
A)  DisableEmptyPass
B)  PermitEmptyPasswords
C)  EmptyPasswordAuth
D)  PermitPasswordLength
B
B. The PermitEmptyPasswords directive specifies whether empty passwords can be usedfor authentication. Enabling empty passwords would be a specialized use case and generallyis not recommended. The other options shown are not valid.
